%% Data Flow Diagram - OpenVINO Model Server (OVMS)
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6
%% Source: architecture/rhoai-2.25/openvino_model_server.md

sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client Application
    participant Istio as Istio Sidecar<br/>(mTLS when enabled)
    participant gRPC as OVMS gRPC Server<br/>configurable/TCP (commonly 8001)
    participant REST as OVMS HTTP Server<br/>configurable/TCP (commonly 8080)
    participant KFS as KFS Frontend<br/>(KServe v2)
    participant TFS as TFS Frontend<br/>(TF Serving)
    participant V3 as V3/OpenAI Handler
    participant SM as ServableManagerModule
    participant MP as MediaPipe Graph<br/>(LLM Calculator)
    participant OV as OpenVINO Runtime
    participant S3 as S3/GCS/Azure<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant HF as HuggingFace Hub<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+

    Note over Client,OV: Flow 1: Standard gRPC Inference Request
    Client->>Istio: gRPC Request (HTTP/2)
    Istio->>gRPC: Forward (plaintext internally)
    gRPC->>KFS: Route to KFS Frontend
    KFS->>SM: Inference Request
    SM->>OV: Execute Inference
    OV-->>SM: Inference Result
    SM-->>KFS: Response
    KFS-->>gRPC: gRPC Response
    gRPC-->>Istio: Response
    Istio-->>Client: gRPC Response

    Note over Client,OV: Flow 2: OpenAI Chat Completion (REST, Streaming)
    Client->>Istio: POST /v3/chat/completions<br/>HTTP/1.1
    Istio->>REST: Forward (plaintext internally)
    REST->>V3: Route to V3 Handler
    V3->>MP: MediaPipe Graph Execution
    MP->>OV: LLM Inference (continuous batching)
    OV-->>MP: Token Generation
    MP-->>V3: Streaming Tokens
    V3-->>REST: SSE Stream Response
    REST-->>Istio: HTTP/1.1 SSE
    Istio-->>Client: Streaming Response (SSE)

    Note over SM,S3: Flow 3: Model Loading from Cloud Storage
    SM->>S3: HTTPS GET (model artifacts)<br/>Auth: AWS IAM / GCP SA / Azure creds
    S3-->>SM: Model Files (TLS 1.2+)
    SM->>OV: Load Model into Runtime

    Note over SM,HF: Flow 4: HuggingFace Model Pull
    SM->>HF: HTTPS GET (model download)<br/>Auth: HF_TOKEN (optional)
    HF-->>SM: Model Artifacts (TLS 1.2+)
    SM->>OV: Convert & Load Model
